http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/RINL-inks-pacts-with-AP/article13995631.ece

RINL, corporate entity of Visakhapatnam Steel Plant, inked MoUs with the State government for an investment of Rs.38,500 crore at the 22{+n}{+d}CII Partnership Summit and first Sunrise AP Investment Meet with an investment of Rs. 38,500 crore.The agreements include expansion of RINL to 7.3 million tonne and modernisation with an investment of Rs 3,600 crore, construction of Coke Oven Battery-5 and other projects at an investment of Rs 3,400 crore. The projects also include further expansion of RINL to 11.5 -12 million tonnes with an estimated investment of Rs. 25,000 crore, establishing a slurry pipeline and pellet plant project (joint venture with NMDC and others at an investment of Rs.6,100 crore and transmission line tower project (JV with POWERGRID) with an investment of Rs.330 crore.The government and RINL agreed on the importance of infrastructure and industrial development in Andhra Pradesh and welcomed mutual cooperation for facilitating investments in AP.Agreements were signed between RINL Director (Projects) P.C. Mohapatra and Kartikeya Misra exchanged the MoU copies for establishing projects to create employment opportunity to around 3,000 people.